issue.title: False Positive: InvalidAttribute
issue.body:
I have discovered what I believe is a false positive when dealing with Attributes. Specifically, I am attempting to get a `ReflectionAttribute` using a `ReflectionMethod`. I am passing an enum where the value is a string representing the type of Attribute to return. I was able to replicate this on https://psalm.dev, see https://psalm.dev/r/c00ee9b5ed.

I believe that if the enum in question was marked as being backed by a `class-string` this would not trigger an error. However, I could not determine a way to do this with the provided annotations.

Thanks, in advance, for taking the time to review this issue!

commits.message:
Refactor internal parsing from static analysis (#55)

* Refactor internal parsing from static analysis

A tremendous amount of effort was having to be maintained to facilitate
static parsing of a codebase for annotations without resorting to
reflection. The effort spent on this didn't have any real value attached
to it outside of choosing when to resolve environment and constant
values. This PR eschews a detailed static analysis of the codebase and
instead uses reflection to determine the appropriate data to gather from
annotations.

This PR also removes the InjectScalar and InjectService annotations as
fixing them to work with this new system would be a fair amount of
effort for something that's being removed with the work on the Inject
annotation.

* Use correct dummy-apps repo
